Class BipartiteGraph.Node<K>

  • java.lang.Object
    • homework2.BipartiteGraph.Node<K>
  • Enclosing class:
    BipartiteGraph<L>

    public class BipartiteGraph.Node<K>
extends java.lang.Object
    A Node is an object containing data and identified by a label. It can have incoming (parent) and outgoing (child) edges. It can be classified as black or not-black.
